# OrderFlow — Data Contracts

> One Postgres, four schemas (`order`, `inventory`, `payment`, `shipment`), per-service DB
> user, zero cross-schema queries. Flyway per schema. All entities carry `created_at`,
> `updated_at`; soft delete (`deleted_at`) where a row is user-meaningful. UUID PKs.
> DDL below is the locked **contract**; exact Flyway SQL is written in Step 5.

## Conventions
- PKs: `uuid` (app-generated, v7-style/time-ordered preferred).
- Timestamps: `timestamptz`, default `now()`. `updated_at` maintained by app/trigger.
- Money: `numeric(12,2)`. Quantities: `integer` (CHECK ≥ 0).
- Enums stored as `varchar` + CHECK (portable, Flyway-friendly) — not native PG enums.
- Optimistic locking: `version integer` (`@Version`) where concurrent writes happen.
- `correlation_id` = `order_id` (the business key threaded through all services + logs + traces).

---

## 1. `order` schema (orchestrator)

### orders
| col | type | notes |
|---|---|---|
| order_id | uuid PK | |
| customer_id | uuid NOT NULL | |
| total_amount | numeric(12,2) NOT NULL CHECK > 0 | |
| status | varchar(32) NOT NULL | overall: PLACED / CONFIRMED / FAILED |
| idempotency_key | varchar(128) NOT NULL | dedup; see Redis note |
| simulate | jsonb NULL | demo failure-injection flags (F-14) |
| created_at / updated_at | timestamptz | |
| deleted_at | timestamptz NULL | soft delete |
- Index: `uq_orders_idempotency (idempotency_key)` UNIQUE (DB backstop to Redis dedup).

### order_items
| col | type | notes |
|---|---|---|
| id | uuid PK | |
| order_id | uuid NOT NULL FK→orders | |
| sku | varchar(64) NOT NULL | |
| qty | integer NOT NULL CHECK > 0 | |
| unit_price | numeric(12,2) NOT NULL CHECK ≥ 0 | |
- Index: `(order_id)`.

### saga_instance  (system of record for saga state)
| col | type | notes |
|---|---|---|
| saga_id | uuid PK | |
| order_id | uuid NOT NULL UNIQUE FK→orders | |
| current_state | varchar(32) NOT NULL | sealed-state name (see §5) |
| version | integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 0 | optimistic lock (D-08) |
| created_at / updated_at | timestamptz | |
- Index: `(current_state)` (dashboard/sweeper queries).

### saga_step  (append-only audit / timeline)
| col | type | notes |
|---|---|---|
| id | uuid PK | |
| saga_id | uuid NOT NULL FK→saga_instance | |
| step | varchar(32) NOT NULL | INVENTORY / PAYMENT / SHIPMENT |
| direction | varchar(16) NOT NULL | FORWARD / COMPENSATION |
| status | varchar(16) NOT NULL | STARTED / SUCCESS / FAILED |
| attempt | integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 1 | |
| correlation_id | uuid NOT NULL | = order_id |
| error | text NULL | failure reason |
| created_at | timestamptz | |
- Index: `(saga_id, created_at)`.

### outbox  (transactional outbox, F-07)
| col | type | notes |
|---|---|---|
| id | uuid PK | |
| aggregate_type | varchar(32) NOT NULL | e.g. ORDER |
| aggregate_id | uuid NOT NULL | order_id |
| topic | varchar(128) NOT NULL | target Kafka topic |
| msg_key | varchar(128) NOT NULL | = order_id (partition key) |
| payload | jsonb NOT NULL | command envelope |
| headers | jsonb NULL | traceparent etc. |
| status | varchar(16) NOT NULL DEFAULT 'PENDING' | PENDING / SENT |
| created_at | timestamptz | |
| published_at | timestamptz NULL | |
- Index: `(status, created_at)` — relay poll (`...WHERE status='PENDING' FOR UPDATE SKIP LOCKED`).

> **Idempotency keys (F-02):** stored in **Redis** (`idem:{key}` → orderId, TTL 24h), not a
> table. `orders.idempotency_key` UNIQUE is the durable backstop.

