## 2. `inventory` schema

### inventory_item
| col | type | notes |
|---|---|---|
| sku | varchar(64) PK | |
| available_qty | integer NOT NULL CHECK ≥ 0 | DB enforces no negative stock |
| reserved_qty | integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 0 CHECK ≥ 0 | |
| version | integer NOT NULL DEFAULT 0 | optimistic lock |
| created_at / updated_at | timestamptz | |

### inventory_reservation  (idempotency by natural key)
| col | type | notes |
|---|---|---|
| id | uuid PK | |
| order_id | uuid NOT NULL | |
| sku | varchar(64) NOT NULL | |
| qty | integer NOT NULL CHECK > 0 | |
| status | varchar(16) NOT NULL | RESERVED / RELEASED |
| created_at / updated_at | timestamptz | |
- `uq_reservation (order_id, sku)` UNIQUE → reserve is idempotent (F-04); release flips
  status, second release is a no-op (F-05).

