## 3. `payment` schema

### payment
| col | type | notes |
|---|---|---|
| id | uuid PK | |
| order_id | uuid NOT NULL UNIQUE | idempotency by order |
| amount | numeric(12,2) NOT NULL CHECK > 0 | |
| status | varchar(16) NOT NULL | CAPTURED / FAILED / REFUNDED |
| failure_reason | varchar(128) NULL | injected-failure label (F-14) |
| created_at / updated_at | timestamptz | |
- Refund idempotent: if already REFUNDED, retried refund is a no-op (F-08).

---

## 4. `shipment` schema

### shipment
| col | type | notes |
|---|---|---|
| id | uuid PK | |
| order_id | uuid NOT NULL UNIQUE | idempotency by order |
| carrier_ref | varchar(64) NULL | mock label id |
| status | varchar(16) NOT NULL | INITIATED / FAILED / CANCELLED |
| failure_reason | varchar(128) NULL | injected fail/hang (F-14) |
| created_at / updated_at | timestamptz | |
- Cancel idempotent: if already CANCELLED, retried cancel is a no-op (F-10).

> **Consumer idempotency (all participants):** natural keys above are the primary guard.
> Optional `processed_message(message_id PK, consumer, processed_at)` inbox table per schema
> as a belt-and-suspenders dedup — included as the documented mechanism for redelivery.

---

## 5. Saga states (sealed interface — F-03)
`OrderPlaced` → `InventoryReserved` → `PaymentCaptured` → `ShipmentInitiated` →
`OrderConfirmed`; failure branch: `Compensating` → `OrderFailed`.
Stored as `saga_instance.current_state` (varchar). Steps: `INVENTORY`, `PAYMENT`, `SHIPMENT`.

---

## 6. REST API contract (order-service)
Base: `/api/orders`. No auth (v1). All errors use the §8 envelope.

| Method | Path | Auth | Body / Params | Success | Errors |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| POST | `/api/orders` | none | `Idempotency-Key` header + `PlaceOrderRequest` | `201 OrderResponse` | 400 invalid, 409 idem-conflict |
| GET | `/api/orders/{id}` | none | — | `200 OrderDetailResponse` | 404 not found |
| GET | `/api/orders` | none | `?page=0&size=20` | `200 Page<OrderSummary>` | 400 bad paging |
| GET | `/api/orders/stream` | none | SSE | `200 text/event-stream` | — |
| GET | `/actuator/health` | none | — | `200` | — |
| GET | `/actuator/prometheus` | none | — | `200` | — |

### DTOs (records)
```
PlaceOrderRequest {
  customerId: UUID,
  items: [ { sku: string, qty: int(>0) } ],   // non-empty
  amount: decimal(>0),
  simulate?: { paymentFail?: bool, shipmentMode?: "ok"|"fail"|"hang" }  // F-14, optional
}
OrderResponse        { orderId: UUID, status: string }                  // 201
OrderSummary         { orderId, customerId, totalAmount, state, updatedAt }
OrderDetailResponse  {
  orderId, customerId, totalAmount, state,
  items: [ { sku, qty, unitPrice } ],
  steps: [ { step, direction, status, attempt, error?, at } ],
  createdAt, updatedAt
}
```
Validation at controller boundary (Jakarta Bean Validation): `@NotNull`, `@Positive`,
`@NotEmpty items`. (≈ .NET DataAnnotations / FluentValidation at the boundary.)

### SSE event (`/api/orders/stream`)
```
event: order-update
data: { orderId, state, steps: [ {step, status} ], totalAmount, updatedAt }
```
Emitted on every saga transition; full snapshot per order (simple for the dashboard).

